RACE.FOOTNOTES: KENTUCKY KISS set the pace along the rail and held firm under a steady drive. STARSHIP AURORA raced off the pace two wide, angled five wide near the quarter pole and finished well. RACHELS SONG was rank at the start, raced off the pace three wide, circled six wide around the far turn and faded in the lane. YANKEE STORM broke a bit awkwardly, trailed in the two path early, went five wide around the far turn and never threatened. MI CORAZON played no factor while racing four and five wide. ANCIENT RELIC was pulling four and five wide, retreated around the far turn and was eased through the lane.
